What Is Pay-Per-Lead in B2B Marketing?
Pay-Per-Lead is a performance-based marketing model where businesses pay a fixed or agreed-upon fee for each qualified lead delivered by a vendor or marketing partner. Unlike cost-per-click (CPC) or cost-per-thousand-impressions (CPM) models, PPL ties your spend directly to pipeline output.

In B2B contexts, a "lead" is not just a name and an email. A qualified B2B lead typically meets specific criteria such as:

Company size and industry
Job title or seniority level
Geographic location
Technology stack or install base
Expressed interest or intent signal
This level of qualification is what separates Pay-Per-Lead from generic lead generation and makes it particularly powerful in complex B2B sales cycles.

